(# DrainGuard Short Judge Documentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Project Title) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**DrainGuard: Smart Urban Drainage Issue Management System**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DrainGuard is a PHP/MySQL role-based urban drainage complaint management system. It allows) Tj
T*
(citizens to submit drainage issues digitally and helps municipal authorities process, route,) Tj
T*
(assign, verify, and close complaints through a structured database-driven workflow. The system) Tj
T*
(uses PHP, MySQLi, MySQL/MariaDB, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap, Bootstrap Icons, and XAMPP.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Problem Statement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Manual drainage complaint handling is slow and difficult to monitor. Citizens often cannot track) Tj
T*
(complaint status properly after reporting a problem. Authorities also face problems in routing) Tj
T*
(complaints to the correct ward, verifying actual maintenance work, and maintaining clear) Tj
T*
(accountability. Without structured audit records, it becomes difficult to identify who handled) Tj
T*
(each step and whether the complaint was properly resolved.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Objective) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main objectives of DrainGuard are:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Digital complaint submission.) Tj
T*
(- Real-time complaint tracking.) Tj
T*
(- Role-wise workflow for all responsible users.) Tj
T*
(- Maintenance team assignment.) Tj
T*
(- Proof upload after work completion.) Tj
T*
(- Inspector verification before final closure.) Tj
T*
(- Citizen feedback and objection handling.) Tj
T*
(- Role-wise notification.) Tj
T*
(- Risk/high-risk area detection.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. User Roles) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| User Role | Main Responsibility |) Tj
T*
(| --- | --- |) Tj
T*
(| Citizen | Submits complaints, tracks status, gives feedback or objection. |) Tj
T*
(| Central Officer | Reviews complaints and routes accepted cases to wards. |) Tj
T*
(| Ward Officer | Verifies complaints, assigns teams, handles objections/disputes. |) Tj
T*
(| Maintenance Team | Starts assigned work and uploads completion proof. |) Tj
T*
(| Inspector | Verifies proof, approves work, or marks false completion. |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 6. Core Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Citizen submits a drainage complaint. The complaint is reviewed by a Central Officer, who) Tj
T*
(accepts or rejects it. Accepted complaints are routed to the proper ward. The Ward Officer) Tj
T*
(verifies the complaint and assigns a maintenance team. The Maintenance Team starts work and) Tj
T*
(uploads completion proof after finishing. The Inspector checks the case and either approves the) Tj
T*
(work or reports false completion. After approval, the Citizen can give feedback or raise an) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
