(objection. Based on feedback or objection, the case is either closed or reopened for further) Tj
T*
(action.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Workflow summary:**) Tj
T*
(Citizen submits complaint -> Central reviews and routes -> Ward verifies and assigns team ->) Tj
T*
(Maintenance starts work and uploads proof -> Inspector verifies -> Citizen gives) Tj
T*
(feedback/objection -> Case closes or reopens.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 7. Database Design Summary) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DrainGuard uses a relational MySQL database. Important table groups include:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- **Users and role tables:** `users`, `citizens`, `central_officers`, `ward_officers`,) Tj
T*
(`maintenance_teams`, `maintenance_team_members`, `inspectors`.) Tj
T*
(- **Location tables:** `cities`, `city_corporations`, `thanas`, `anchals`, `wards`, `areas`,) Tj
T*
(`locations`, `drains`.) Tj
T*
(- **Complaint tables:** `complaints`, `complaint_media`, `complaint_status_logs`,) Tj
T*
(`complaint_decisions`, `issues`, `affected_areas`.) Tj
T*
(- **Assignment and maintenance tables:** `complaint_assignments`, `maintenance_proofs`,) Tj
T*
(`maintenance_support_requests`.) Tj
T*
(- **Inspection, feedback, and reopen tables:** `inspection_logs`, `feedbacks`,) Tj
T*
(`reopen_requests`, `false_completion_reviews`, `maintenance_team_reviews`.) Tj
T*
(- **Notification tables:** `citizen_notifications`, `central_notifications`,) Tj
T*
(`ward_notifications`, `maintenance_notifications`, `inspector_notifications`.) Tj
T*
(- **Risk and instruction tables:** `risk`, `role_instructions`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The `complaints` table is the main transaction table, while `users` is the central login table.) Tj
T*
(Assignment, proof, inspection, feedback, notification, and log tables help track the full) Tj
T*
(complaint lifecycle.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 8. Advanced DBMS Topics Used) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Transaction Management) Tj
T*
(- ACID Properties) Tj
T*
(- Commit and Rollback) Tj
T*
(- Prepared Statement) Tj
T*
(- JOIN, filtering, and subquery) Tj
T*
(- Indexing) Tj
T*
(- Authentication) Tj
T*
(- Authorization / Role-based access) Tj
T*
(- Audit log / Status log) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 9. Conclusion) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DrainGuard is a transparent, accountable, and database-driven urban drainage complaint) Tj
T*
(management system. It tracks the complete complaint lifecycle from citizen submission to central) Tj
T*
(review, ward routing, maintenance work, proof upload, inspector verification, feedback,) Tj
T*
(objection, and final closure or reopening. For a DBMS project show, it demonstrates practical) Tj
T*
(use of relational database design, role-based access, notifications, audit logs, and workflow) Tj
T*
(management.) Tj
T*
ET
